<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,404,1151]" pageId="5" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,618,548,575]" pageId="5" pageNumber="47">
Diagnostic description of 
<typeStatus box="[504,613,549,575]" pageId="5" pageNumber="47">lectotype</typeStatus>
.
</emphasis>
Integument black; head with somewhat paler anterior portions; antennomeres 1–4, front legs, middle legs and terminal spines of metatibiae yellowish; hind legs reddish brown; pubescence yellowish. Antennomeres 5–10 ca. 1.50× as long as wide. Lateral carinae of pronotum concave in lateral aspect. Metatibiae with two long oblique lateral ridges. Metatarsomere 1 with two ridges; metatarsomere 2 with one ridge. Outer terminal spine of metatibiae short, ca. 2/3 of width of metatarsomere 1.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,404,1151]" box="[199,693,728,755]" pageId="5" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,381,728,755]" pageId="5" pageNumber="47">Current status.</emphasis>
Valid species (
<emphasis bold="true" box="[550,677,728,755]" pageId="5" pageNumber="47">stat. restit.</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="47" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,404,1151]" pageId="5" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,765,791]" pageId="5" pageNumber="47">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Emery, M. C." box="[323,480,765,792]" pageId="5" pageNumber="47" pagination="1 - 128" refId="ref5127" refString="Emery, M. C. (1876) Essai monographique sur les mordellides de l'Europe et des contrees limitrophes. L'Abeille, Journal d'Entomologie, 14, 1 - 128." type="journal article" year="1876">Emery (1876)</bibRefCitation>
and all subsequent authors considered 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Costa" authorityYear="1854" box="[925,1168,765,791]" class="Insecta" family="Mordellidae" genus="Mordellistena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="picipes">
<emphasis box="[925,1168,765,791]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="47">Mordellistena picipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Gyllenhal, 1827)" baseAuthorityName="Gyllenhal" baseAuthorityYear="1827" box="[151,617,801,827]" class="Insecta" family="Mordellidae" genus="Mordellistena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parvula">
<emphasis box="[151,403,801,827]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="47">Mordellistena parvula</emphasis>
(Gyllenhal, 1827)
</taxonomicName>
. However, a recent re-examination of the 
<typeStatus box="[1102,1205,801,827]" pageId="5" pageNumber="47">lectotype</typeStatus>
revealed significant differences between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Costa" authorityYear="1854" box="[383,499,838,863]" class="Insecta" family="Mordellidae" genus="Mordellistena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="picipes">
<emphasis box="[383,499,838,863]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="47">M. picipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Gyllenhal" baseAuthorityYear="1827" box="[554,679,837,863]" class="Insecta" family="Mordellidae" genus="Mordellistena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parvula">
<emphasis box="[554,679,837,863]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="47">M. parvula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(type specimen examined, UUZM) in the form of lateral carinae of pronotum and colouration of the legs. Such differences lead us to consider 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Costa" authorityYear="1854" box="[990,1190,873,899]" class="Insecta" family="Mordellidae" genus="Mordellistena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="picipes">
<emphasis box="[990,1021,874,899]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="47">M.</emphasis>
(s. str.) 
<emphasis box="[1111,1190,874,899]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="47">picipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a valid species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,404,1151]" pageId="5" pageNumber="47">
<bibRefCitation author="Mulsant, M. E." box="[199,371,908,935]" pageId="5" pageNumber="47" pagination="305 - 471" refId="ref5183" refString="Mulsant, M. E. (1856) Histoire naturelle des coleopteres de France. Longipedes. Annales de la Societe Linneenne de Lyon, Nouvelle Serie, 3, 305 - 471." type="journal article" year="1856">Mulsant (1856)</bibRefCitation>
listed 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Costa" authorityYear="1854" box="[443,559,910,935]" class="Insecta" family="Mordellidae" genus="Mordellistena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="picipes">
<emphasis box="[443,559,910,935]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="47">M. picipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a variety of 
<taxonomicName authority="Mulsant, 1856" authorityName="Mulsant" authorityYear="1856" box="[724,1043,908,935]" class="Insecta" family="Mordellidae" genus="Mordellistena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inaequalis">
<emphasis box="[724,877,909,935]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="47">M. inaequalis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Mulsant, M. E." box="[883,1043,908,935]" pageId="5" pageNumber="47" pagination="305 - 471" refId="ref5183" refString="Mulsant, M. E. (1856) Histoire naturelle des coleopteres de France. Longipedes. Annales de la Societe Linneenne de Lyon, Nouvelle Serie, 3, 305 - 471." type="journal article" year="1856">Mulsant, 1856</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
disregarding the earlier description date of the former. According to the rules of 
<bibRefCitation author="ICZN" box="[654,804,945,971]" pageId="5" pageNumber="47" refId="ref5218" refString="ICZN (1999) International Code of Zoological Nomenclature (4 th edn). International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London, xxix + 306 pp." type="book" year="1999">ICZN (1999)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mulsant" authorityYear="1856" box="[816,971,945,971]" class="Insecta" family="Mordellidae" genus="Mordellistena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inaequalis">
<emphasis box="[816,971,945,971]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="47">M. inaequalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be treated as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Costa" authorityYear="1854" box="[151,267,982,1007]" class="Insecta" family="Mordellidae" genus="Mordellistena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="picipes">
<emphasis box="[151,267,982,1007]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="47">M. picipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, we cannot confirm the status here because most of the Mulsant’s 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[1115,1252,981,1007]" class="Insecta" family="Mordellidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Mordellidae</taxonomicName>
<typeStatus box="[1258,1320,981,1007]" pageId="5" pageNumber="47">types</typeStatus>
, including those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mulsant" authorityYear="1856" box="[248,402,1017,1043]" class="Insecta" family="Mordellidae" genus="Mordellistena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inaequalis">
<emphasis box="[248,402,1017,1043]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="47">M. inaequalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, have not yet been found.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,404,1151]" pageId="5" pageNumber="47">
The 
<typeStatus box="[249,352,1053,1079]" pageId="5" pageNumber="47">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Costa" authorityYear="1854" box="[388,504,1054,1079]" class="Insecta" family="Mordellidae" genus="Mordellistena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="picipes">
<emphasis box="[388,504,1054,1079]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="47">M. picipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
closely resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Ermisch, 1956" authorityName="Ermisch" authorityYear="1956" box="[715,1091,1052,1079]" class="Insecta" family="Mordellidae" genus="Mordellistena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pseudoparvula">
<emphasis box="[715,918,1053,1079]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="47">M. pseudoparvula</emphasis>
Ermisch, 1956
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Ermisch, 1967" authorityName="Ermisch" authorityYear="1967" box="[1101,1436,1053,1079]" class="Insecta" family="Mordellidae" genus="Mordellistena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inexpectata">
<emphasis box="[1101,1267,1054,1079]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="47">M. inexpectata</emphasis>
Ermisch, 1967
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Shchegoleva-Barovskaya, 1930" authorityName="Shchegoleva-Barovskaya" authorityYear="1930" box="[198,751,1089,1115]" class="Insecta" family="Mordellidae" genus="Mordellistena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parvuliformis">
<emphasis box="[198,387,1089,1115]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="47">M. parvuliformis</emphasis>
Shchegoleva-Barovskaya, 1930
</taxonomicName>
. Therefore, the validity of these species must be reconsidered in the future.
</paragraph>
